name: Pinsir
flavorText: Although it's tough, it can't handle cold well. When night falls, it buries itself in leafage and sleeps.
Ability1Text: Damage from your Single Strike Pokémon's attacks isn't affected by your opponent's Active Pokémon's Resistance.

name: Hoppip
flavorText: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Skiploom
flavorText: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.
Ability1Text: When you attach an Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Jumpluff
flavorText: Even in the fiercest wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon may attack twice each turn. If the first attack Knocks Out your opponent's Active Pokémon, you may attack again after your opponent chooses a new Active Pokémon.

name: Seedot
flavorText: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.
Attack1Text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck.

name: Tropius
flavorText: Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon during their last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Leafeon V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Grass Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Leafeon VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Petilil
flavorText: They prefer clean water and soil. When the environment they live in turns bad, the whole bunch will up and move to a new area.

name: Lilligant
flavorText: It's well liked by other Pokémon because of its beauty. The flower on its head needs constant care, or it will soon wither and rot.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep. If tails, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Dwebble
flavorText: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Crustle
flavorText: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They're mighty enough to crack Rhyperior's carapace.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Trevenant V
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Trevenant VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage for each Supporter card in your opponent's discard pile.

name: Gossifleur
flavorText: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Eldegoss
flavorText: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Applin
flavorText: As soon as it's born, it burrows into an apple. Not only does the apple serve as its food source, but the flavor of the fruit determines its evolution.

name: Flareon VMAX
Attack1Text: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck. This attack does 100 damage for each Energy card you discarded in this way.

name: Entei
flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage for each damage counter on all of your Benched Single Strike Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Victini
flavorText: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.
Attack1Text: You may search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Volcarona V
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each basic Energy card in your discard pile. Then, shuffle those Energy cards into your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Litleo
flavorText: This hot-blooded Pokémon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.

name: Pyroar
flavorText: The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn't use it on its prey. This Pokémon prefers to eat raw meat.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: It has been found that its brain cells are 10 times more active when Psyduck is experiencing a headache.

name: Golduck
flavorText: A professional swimmer, it can continue swimming for two days straight by waving its long tail skillfully.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Tentacool
flavorText: Its body is 99% water. The remaining 1% contains the organ that makes its poison.

name: Tentacruel
flavorText: It communicates with others of its kind by lighting up the red orbs on its head. When the orbs are blinking, it's a warning sign.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Gyarados V
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Gyarados VMAX
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Vaporeon VMAX
Attack1Text: Put a Water Pokémon from your discard pile onto your Bench. If you do, attach up to 3 Water Energy cards from your discard pile to that Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Suicune V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Lotad
flavorText: Its leaf grew too large for it to live on land. That is how it began to live floating in the water.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Lombre
flavorText: It lives at the water's edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass by day and becomes active at night.

name: Ludicolo
flavorText: If it hears festive music, it begins moving in rhythm in order to amplify its power.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may use this Ability. During this turn, your Basic Pokémon's attacks do 100 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Carvanha
flavorText: With its sturdy jaws and fangs, it can easily chomp wooden boats to splinters. It fights with Basculin over food.

name: Sharpedo
flavorText: It drinks in seawater and jets it from its rear to propel itself. It's very sensitive to the scent of blood.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Feebas
flavorText: It is a shabby and ugly Pokémon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Milotic
flavorText: It's said that a glimpse of a Milotic and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you're feeling.
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent plays a Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to you or your hand.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

name: Luvdisc
flavorText: Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola's branches.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a card for each card in your opponent's hand.

name: Glaceon V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard a Stadium in play.

name: Glaceon VMAX
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon VMAX, except any Glaceon VMAX.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Tympole
flavorText: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can't hear its cries of warning.

name: Cryogonal
flavorText: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 6 cards of your deck and attach any number of basic Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Bergmite
flavorText: This Pokémon lives in areas of frigid cold. It secures itself to the back of an Avalugg by freezing its feet in place.

name: Avalugg
flavorText: As Avalugg moves about during the day, the cracks in its body deepen. The Pokémon's body returns to a pristine state overnight.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Wishiwashi
flavorText: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has 3 or more Water Energy attached, it gets +150 HP.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each basic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Eiscue
flavorText: This Pokémon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Basic Pokémon.

name: Arctovish V
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Pokémon V or a Pokémon-GX, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When Pikachu meet, they'll touch their tails together and exchange electricity through them as a form of greeting.
Attack1Text: Attach a Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

name: Raichu
flavorText: If its electric pouches run empty, it raises its tail to gather electricity from the atmosphere.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to each Pokémon V and Pokémon-GX (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Jolteon VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack also does 100 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Chinchou
flavorText: On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.

name: Lanturn
flavorText: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokémon tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

name: Mareep
flavorText: Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You'll want to pet it because it's cute, but if you use your bare hand, you'll get a painful shock.

name: Flaaffy
flavorText: It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Ampharos
flavorText: Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: You may discard 3 Lightning Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Emolga
flavorText: As it flies, it scatters electricity around, so bird Pokémon keep their distance. That's why Emolga can keep all its food to itself.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Dracozolt V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, Energy cards can't be attached from your opponent's hand to the Defending Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck.

name: Dracozolt VMAX
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 12 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

name: Regieleki
flavorText: Its entire body is made up of a single organ that generates electrical energy. Regieleki is capable of creating all Galar's electricity.
Attack2Text: Discard all Lightning Energy from this Pokémon. This attack also does 40 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Drowzee
flavorText: It puts its prey to sleep and devours their dreams. It seems that bad dreams taste sour, so Drowzee doesn't particularly like eating them.

name: Hypno
flavorText: There are some Hypno that assist doctors with patients who can't sleep at night in hospitals.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 90 more damage. Then, that Pokémon recovers from all Special Conditions.

name: Galarian Articuno
flavorText: Known as Articuno, this Pokémon fires beams that can immobilize opponents as if they had been frozen solid.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may attach up to 2 Psychic Energy cards from your hand to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Discard all Psychic Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Espeon V
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon V. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Espeon VMAX
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to all of your Pokémon that have Energy attached.(Existing effects are not removed. Damage is not an effect.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Wobbuffet
flavorText: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.
Attack1Text: Put damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon equal to the number of damage counters on 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Sableye
flavorText: It feeds on gemstone crystals. In darkness, its eyes sparkle with the glitter of jewels.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Trainer card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Woobat
flavorText: It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Swoobat
flavorText: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon's nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.
Attack1Text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Golurk V
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an evolved Pokémon, devolve it by putting the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent's hand.

name: Flabébé
flavorText: Flabébé wears a crown made from pollen it's collected from its flower. The crown has hidden healing properties.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Floette
flavorText: It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

name: Florges
flavorText: Its life can span several hundred years. It's said to devote its entire life to protecting gardens.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move an Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to 1 of your Rapid Strike Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Sylveon V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.

name: Sylveon VMAX
Attack1Text: Attach an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, heal 120 damage from that Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each different type of Pokémon on your Bench.

name: Pumpkaboo
flavorText: The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokémon that see it.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may discard a Stadium in play.

name: Gourgeist
flavorText: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.
Attack1Text: Reveal the top 6 cards of your deck. This attack does 60 damage for each Psychic Pokémon you find there. Then, shuffle those Pokémon back into your deck and discard the other cards.

name: Cutiefly
flavorText: An opponent's aura can tell Cutiefly what that opponent's next move will be. Then Cutiefly can glide around the attack and strike back.

name: Ribombee
flavorText: Ribombee absolutely hate getting wet or rained on. In the cloudy Galar region, they are very seldom seen.
Attack1Text: You may move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Marshadow
flavorText: It sinks into the shadows of people and Pokémon, where it can understand their feelings and copy their capabilities.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Rapid Strike cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out during your next turn, take 1 more Prize card.

name: Hitmonchan
flavorText: Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Galarian Zapdos
flavorText: One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. Supposedly, this Pokémon runs through the mountains at over 180 mph.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may attach up to 2 Fighting Energy cards from your hand to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: You may discard all Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Medicham V
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If your opponent's Pokémon is Knocked Out by this attack, take another turn after this one. (Skip Pokémon Checkup.) If 1 of your Pokémon used Yoga Loop during your last turn, this attack can't be used.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Hippopotas
flavorText: This Pokémon is active during the day and passes the cold desert nights burrowed snugly into the sand.

name: Hippowdon
flavorText: When roused to violence by its rage, it spews out the quantities of sand it has swallowed and whips up a sandstorm.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Roggenrola
flavorText: When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.

name: Boldore
flavorText: It relies on sound in order to monitor what's in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it's facing.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Gigalith
flavorText: Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck, they have a limitation— they can only be fired when the sun is out.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 50 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself for each damage counter on it.

name: Palpitoad
flavorText: On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.

name: Seismitoad
flavorText: This Pokémon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless more, and its Retreat Cost is Colorless more.

name: Lycanroc V
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Lycanroc VMAX
Attack1Text: Knock Out 1 of your opponent's Pokémon in play that has 60 HP or less remaining.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Galarian Moltres
flavorText: The sinister aura that blazes like molten fire around this Pokémon is what inspired the name Moltres.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may attach up to 2 Darkness Energy cards from your hand to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Umbreon V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Umbreon VMAX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

name: Nuzleaf
flavorText: They live in holes bored in large trees. The sound of Nuzleaf's grass flute fills listeners with dread.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Shiftry
flavorText: It lives quietly in the deep forest. It is said to create chilly winter winds with the fans it holds.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has any damage counters on it, put it and all attached cards into your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Scraggy
flavorText: It protects itself with its durable skin. It's thought that this Pokémon will evolve once its skin has completely stretched out.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 10 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Scrafty
flavorText: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Garbodor V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Garbodor VMAX
Ability1Text: This Pokémon may have up to 2 Pokémon Tools attached to it. If it loses this Ability, discard Pokémon Tools from it until only 1 remains.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Zorua
flavorText: If a normally talkative child suddenly stops talking, it may have been replaced by Zorua.

name: Zoroark
flavorText: If it thinks humans are going to discover its den, Zoroark shows them visions that make them wander around in the woods.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may choose a Stage 1 Pokémon, except any Zoroark, from your discard pile. If you do, discard this Pokémon and all attached cards, and put the chosen Pokémon in its place.

name: Nickit
flavorText: Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.

name: Thievul
flavorText: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may have each player shuffle their hand and put it on the bottom of their deck. If either player put any cards on the bottom of their deck in this way, each player draws 4 cards.

name: Altaria
flavorText: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, shuffle your deck, then put that card on top of it.

name: Bagon
flavorText: Some theories suggest that its behavior of forcefully bashing its head into things stimulates cells that affect its evolution.

name: Shelgon
flavorText: Shelgon lives deep within caves. It stays shut up in its hard shell, dreaming of the day it will be able to fly.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Salamence
flavorText: Thanks to its fervent wishes, the cells in its body finally mutated, and at last it has its heart's desire—wings.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may have your opponent switch their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Rayquaza V
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.
Attack2Text: You may discard up to 2 basic Fire Energy or up to 2 basic Lightning Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 80 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Rayquaza VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may discard your hand and draw 3 cards.
Attack1Text: You may discard any amount of basic Fire Energy or any amount of basic Lightning Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 80 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Dialga
flavorText: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Pokémon V, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Deino
flavorText: Because it can't see, this Pokémon is constantly biting at everything it touches, trying to keep track of its surroundings.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Zweilous
flavorText: Their two heads will fight each other over a single piece of food. Zweilous are covered in scars even without battling others.

name: Hydreigon
flavorText: The three heads take turns sinking their teeth into the opponent. Their attacks won't slow until their target goes down.
Attack1Text: This attack does 100 more damage for each Prize card your opponent took during their last turn.

name: Kyurem
flavorText: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.
Attack1Text: Discard any amount of Water Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Noivern V
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Prize card your opponent has taken. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Drampa
flavorText: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it's angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.
Attack2Text: If your Benched Pokémon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Flapple
flavorText: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your opponent's Pokémon in play that has an Ability.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon V, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Appletun
flavorText: Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.
Attack1Text: This attack does 70 damage for each Special Energy card attached to your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon V, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Duraludon V
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks do 30 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Duraludon VMAX
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon that have Special Energy attached.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Regidrago
flavorText: Its body is composed of crystallized dragon energy. Regidrago is said to have the powers of every dragon Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Pokémon V, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Teddiursa
flavorText: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.

name: Ursaring
